\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\lang9 # MARBINE MEMORIES\par
\par
## Software Requirements Specification (SRS)\par
\par
### Project Information\par
\par
**Project Name:** Marbine Memories\par
\par
**Version:** 1.0\par
\par
**Prepared By:** Marc\par
\par
**Technology Stack:**\par
\par
* Frontend: React.js\par
* Backend: Node.js + Express.js\par
* Database: MySQL\par
* Authentication: JWT\par
* Hosting: Vercel (Frontend) & VPS/Render (Backend)\par
\par
---\par
\par
# 1. Introduction\par
\par
## 1.1 Purpose\par
\par
Marbine Memories is a private web application designed to preserve and celebrate the journey of Marc and Blandine. The platform will serve as a digital space where memories, photos, messages, milestones, and future goals can be stored and shared securely.\par
\par
## 1.2 Goals\par
\par
* Create a personalized memory-sharing platform.\par
* Store relationship milestones and achievements.\par
* Provide a private gallery for photos and videos.\par
* Enable secure message sharing.\par
* Track important dates and anniversaries.\par
* Build a meaningful software project under the "Marbine" identity.\par
\par
---\par
\par
# 2. System Overview\par
\par
The system consists of:\par
\par
### Frontend Application\par
\par
Developed using React.js.\par
\par
Responsibilities:\par
\par
* User Interface\par
* Dashboard\par
* Gallery Display\par
* Timeline Visualization\par
* Profile Management\par
\par
### Backend API\par
\par
Developed using Node.js and Express.js.\par
\par
Responsibilities:\par
\par
* Authentication\par
* Data Processing\par
* File Upload Management\par
* Database Communication\par
\par
### Database\par
\par
MySQL Database\par
\par
Responsibilities:\par
\par
* User Management\par
* Memory Storage\par
* Message Storage\par
* Timeline Events\par
* Media Metadata\par
\par
---\par
\par
# 3. Functional Requirements\par
\par
## 3.1 User Authentication\par
\par
Features:\par
\par
* User Registration\par
* User Login\par
* JWT Authentication\par
* Password Encryption using bcrypt\par
* Logout Functionality\par
\par
---\par
\par
## 3.2 User Profiles\par
\par
Each user can:\par
\par
* View profile\par
* Update profile information\par
* Upload profile picture\par
* Change password\par
\par
Fields:\par
\par
* Full Name\par
* Email\par
* Bio\par
* Profile Image\par
\par
---\par
\par
## 3.3 Memories Management\par
\par
Users can:\par
\par
* Add memories\par
* Edit memories\par
* Delete memories\par
* Categorize memories\par
\par
Memory Fields:\par
\par
* Title\par
* Description\par
* Date\par
* Location\par
* Image\par
* Category\par
\par
---\par
\par
## 3.4 Gallery Module\par
\par
Features:\par
\par
* Upload photos\par
* Upload videos\par
* View gallery\par
* Filter by category\par
* Download media\par
\par
Supported Formats:\par
\par
* JPG\par
* PNG\par
* JPEG\par
* MP4\par
\par
---\par
\par
## 3.5 Timeline Module\par
\par
Features:\par
\par
* Create milestone events\par
* Display chronological timeline\par
* Edit timeline entries\par
\par
Examples:\par
\par
* First Meeting\par
* Graduation Day\par
* First Project Together\par
* Anniversary\par
\par
---\par
\par
## 3.6 Love Notes Module\par
\par
Features:\par
\par
* Send private notes\par
* Save favorite messages\par
* Search messages\par
\par
Fields:\par
\par
* Sender\par
* Receiver\par
* Subject\par
* Message\par
* Date\par
\par
---\par
\par
## 3.7 Anniversary Counter\par
\par
Features:\par
\par
* Calculate days together\par
* Calculate months together\par
* Calculate years together\par
* Countdown to next anniversary\par
\par
---\par
\par
## 3.8 Future Goals Module\par
\par
Features:\par
\par
* Create goals\par
* Update progress\par
* Mark completed goals\par
\par
Examples:\par
\par
* Launch Startup\par
* Build SaaS Product\par
* Travel Together\par
* Complete New Certification\par
\par
---\par
\par
# 4. Non-Functional Requirements\par
\par
### Security\par
\par
* JWT Authentication\par
* Password Hashing\par
* SQL Injection Protection\par
* XSS Protection\par
* HTTPS Communication\par
\par
### Performance\par
\par
* API Response Time < 2 Seconds\par
* Optimized Database Queries\par
* Lazy Loading Images\par
\par
### Scalability\par
\par
* Modular Architecture\par
* RESTful APIs\par
* Reusable React Components\par
\par
---\par
\par
